    {
      "instruction": "<p>Reduce the heat to medium and add the <strong>chopped onion</strong>, <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and <strong>cornflour</strong> and give everything a good mix</p><p>Add 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[550ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>with your <strong>beef stock mix</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and put the dish in the oven, covered, and cook for an initial 50 min or until the sauce has thickened and the beef is cooked through – this is your <strong>Chinese-style braised beef</strong></p>",
